source.name: Hospital Process of Care Measures – Children’s Asthma
source.description: A list of hospitals and their quality measure ratings related to children’s asthma care. Asthma is a chronic lung condition that causes problems getting air in and out of the lungs. Children with asthma may experience wheezing, coughing, chest tightness and trouble breathing.
